                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Nelson, Bert N./42: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-09T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 9, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 9—1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. My 130, December 8, 2 p.m. The following telegram has been sent to the
                    Legation: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 9, 4 p.m. My December 8, 2 p.m. I sent Consul Lewis Clark to
                            Sinyangchow this morning to cooperate with and advise Dr. Skinsnes in
                            connection with efforts to release Reverend Nelson and his co-worker
                            Tvedt.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to the Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
